$ /etc/passwd

→ Linux/user[User] account information: each line represents a user and is colon-separated with the following fields:

table { ll
  username ☰
  → development/security/password[password] ☰ nowadays usually `x`, see `→ Linux/fhs/etc/shadow` 
  user id ☰
  default → Linux/group[group] id ☰ See `→ Linux/fhs/etc/group`
  gecos ☰
  The user's → Linux/home-directory ☰
  The shell ☰ The name of the program to be run when a user logs in, usually a → Linux/shell.
table }

In order to prohibit a user from logging in, the programm to be launched (7) might be set to `/bin/false`

The file should be edited with `→ Linux/shell/commands/vipw`.

sa:
 `→ Linux/fhs/etc/group`


  → Linux/shell/commands[Shell commands]
    • `→ Linux/shell/commands/usermod`
    • `→ Linux/shell/commands/useradd`
    • `→ Linux/shell/commands/chpasswd`
    • `→ Linux/shell/commands/passwd`
    • `→ Linux/shell/commands/getent`
    • `lslogins` (part of → Linux/utilities#util-linux).

 `→ Linux/fhs/usr/share/doc/base-passwd/users-and-groups_txt_gz`
